These are the scripts for easy installation of all the entire lib_hao:

1. Download lib_hao_install : "git clone https://github.com/hshi/lib_hao_install" 


2. Download all the lib_hao libraries: "python download.py"


3. Install the lib_hao libraries: "python install type"
   "type" can be: mpi, serial, storm, hu, hu+magma
   You can build your own "type" in cmake.py for different platform.


4. Test the lib hao:
   0) If you are in a cluster, first require an interactive job, e.g.
      "qsub -X -I -l walltime=1:00:00 -l nodes=1:wind:ppn=16"

   1) Go to the lib_hao install prefix directory (can be found in cmake.py)
   
   2) "cd test"
 
   3) "python Path/to/lib_hao_install/runtest.py type"   "type" can be found in runtest.py.


5) Clean the lib_hao_install directory: "python clean.py"



Dependence:
   1) fftw_lib_hao 
       need fftw library, and FFTW=/PATH/TO/FFTW, e.g. export FFTW='/opt/fftw'

   2) matrix_lib_hao 
       Need mkl library, and MKL=/PATH/TO/MKL, e.g. export MKL='/opt/intel/mkl' "
       Or need acml library, and ACML=/PATH/TO/ACML, e.g. export ACML='/usr/local/acml-5.1.0/' 
       Need magma library(optional), and MAGMA=/PATH/TO/MAGMA, e.g. export MAGMA='/usr/local/intel64/nehalem/magma-1.3.0'

   3) mpi_lib_hao
       Need mpi.

   4. random_lib_hao
       Need sprng library, and SPRNG=/PATH/TO/SPRNG, e.g. export SPRNG='/home/username/sprng/sprng2.0'
       Need gmp library, and GMP=/PATH/TO/GMP, e.g. export GMP='/usr/local/gmp-4.3.2'.

Feel free to change the script for your own application, enjoy your coding.
